ProMED Rapporteur Mahmoud Orabi

******
[2]
Date: Sun 24 Apr 2022
Source: Al Mada [in Arabic, machine trans., edited]
https://almadapaper.net/view.php?cat=263573


Yesterday, Sunday [24 Apr 2022], the Dhi Qar Health Department confirmed the continuation of the crisis cell formed by the governor to work on the control of the hemorrhagic fever, while calling for the intervention of the security forces to implement isolation measures in the affected areas.

The director of the Public Health Department in the Dhi Qar Health Department, Hussein Riyad, said in an interview with Al-Mada, that "the governorate recorded 24 cases last year [2021], including 9 deaths, while the current year [2022] witnessed the registration of 8 cases, including 3 deaths."

Riyadh added, "The suspected cases are sampled and examined in the central laboratory in Baghdad," noting that "we have in the Dhi Qar Health Department one isolation hall, and are working to develop it during the coming period."

He added that "the affected areas must be isolated in order to stop the [spread the infection of the] hemorrhagic fever" noting that "we need the intervention of the security forces to implement isolation measures and help protect citizens from disease."

The director of the Public Health Department in Dhi Qar added that "the governorate is complaining about the lack of a modern and sanitary slaughterhouse, which made diseases spread quickly." Riyadh indicated that "the crisis cell formed by the governor is working to control the disease", pointing out that "there are other efforts being made by the veterinary medicine that follows up on the cases of the animals that transmit this disease to humans."

